  32.4.21 ESMF_LocStreamIsCreated - Check whether a LocStream object has been
  created

   INTERFACE:
   function ESMF_LocStreamIsCreated(locstream, rc)

   RETURN VALUE:
     logical :: ESMF_LocStreamIsCreated

   ARGUMENTS:
     type(ESMF_LocStream), intent(in)            :: locstream
 -- The following arguments require argument keyword syntax (e.g. rc=rc). --
     integer,             intent(out), optional :: rc

   DESCRIPTION:

   Return .true. if the locstream has been created. Otherwise return
   .false.. If an error occurs, i.e. rc /= ESMF_SUCCESS is returned, the
   return value of the function will also be .false..

   The arguments are:

   locstream
          ESMF_LocStream queried.

   [rc]
          Return code; equals ESMF_SUCCESS if there are no errors.

